==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Humpbacked salmon
<hw>Hump"backed` salm"on</hw>. <def>A small salmon (<spn>Oncorhynchus
gorbuscha</spn>) which ascends the rivers of the Pacific coast from
California to Alaska, and also on the Asiatic side. In the breeding
season the male has a large dorsal hump and distorted jaws.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Humpback whale</ent>⟦br⟧
